<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="1747" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1747">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 718.1915/224.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Cresson</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-27">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 27, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s telegram November 25. I have received from the Minister of
                            Foreign Affairs assurances no change in status quo has occurred or is
                            contemplated on Costa Rican boundary. New officials instructed to this
                            effect were lately on Pacific side but no newly created offices.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cresson</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>